Dependencies
============

Dependencies should be automatically pulled in when installing Tasty. If you
prefer using another installation method for the dependencies, install these
packages.

- python-2.6 : http://python.org
- gmpy : http://gmpy.sourceforge.net/
- epydoc : http://epydoc.sourceforge.net/
- pylint : http://www.logilab.org/project/pylint/

(WINDOWS)
- WMI : http://timgolden.me.uk/python/downloads/WMI-1.4.5.zip

Installation
============

Installation via setuptools::

easy_install -Z tasty

Installation via distutils::

Change current directory to your copy of tasty::

    cd /path/to/tasty

Install into system path::

    python setup.py install

Local developer mode installation::

    python setup.py develop

Getting apidocs
===============
In order to read the api docs, you have to generate it first. You will find
them in docs/api.

e.g. html format::

    python setup.py apidoc

pdf format::

    python setup.py apidoc -f pdf

Testing code
============
Optionally run all tests on tasty::

    python setup.py test

We also provide code style validation::

    python setup.py check

Aliases
=======
All aliases are defined in setup.cfg

Installs tasty and builds the apidocs in several formats::

    python setup.py all

Process all tests at once::

    python setup.py qa

Using all + qa::

    python setup.py full

Misc
====

For more information about setup.py commands::

    python setup.py --help-commands


Using Tasty
===========

For further information about using tasty, please see README document.
